# Production Standards — Non-Negotiable

## These are live production applications

- **Tiltbox** is a live iOS app published on the Apple App Store with real users.
- **Axiom** is the live production API that Tiltbox depends on.
- Neither project is a hobby, test environment, or pre-launch product.
- Every change made here affects real users immediately.

## Code of conduct for every change

- **Never apply a band-aid fix.** If the root cause is not fully understood, stop and investigate further before writing a single line.
- **Never patch a symptom** while leaving the underlying problem in place. Patches break again. Root cause fixes do not.
- **Slow down before acting.** Read all relevant files. Understand the full picture. Then fix.
- **Never deploy untested logic** to the live API hoping it will work.
- **Never run two fixes in sequence** without confirming the first one worked.
- **Always explain what you are doing and why before doing it**, and wait for confirmation when the change is significant.

## Specific rules for this project

- Schema migrations (ALTER TABLE) are one-time operations. They must never run inside the daily pipeline.
- The daily pipeline must be fully end-to-end tested (not just code-reviewed) before declaring it working.
- If a pipeline run produces 0 pitchers or fails silently, that is a critical failure — not a warning.
- The self-healing auto-trigger in routes.py must never corrupt the main database session.
